WEBVTT

00:02.319 --> 00:04.488
Chief: He's suffering
from sombialysis.

00:04.556 --> 00:07.327
It's a rare neurological
condition that causes him to

00:07.362 --> 00:08.965
spontaneously burst into song.

00:09.034 --> 00:10.667
But I can cure him, Sy.

00:10.702 --> 00:12.670
I was born to do this operation.

00:12.706 --> 00:14.206
Sy: It's a little too risky.

00:14.241 --> 00:16.776
Chief: If I fail, I will happily
turn in my resignation.

00:16.812 --> 00:19.580
Sy: And I will take it, but
with a lot less happiness than

00:19.615 --> 00:22.051
that with which you <i>claim</i> 
you're handing it to me.

00:22.086 --> 00:24.053
Chief: I love the
'stache, by the way.

00:24.089 --> 00:24.721
Sy: Thank you.

00:24.790 --> 00:27.358
Chief: At the risk of
sounding a <i>bit</i> like a broken

00:27.427 --> 00:35.000
record, I want to assure you all that
I...was...born to do this operation.

00:35.068 --> 00:37.068
Let's get cracking. Yes.

00:37.137 --> 00:38.436
Ha ha!

00:38.472 --> 00:41.608
Here we come.

00:41.643 --> 00:43.611
Steady as she goes.

00:43.646 --> 00:44.612
[ All gasp ]

00:44.648 --> 00:45.780
Scalpel.

00:45.816 --> 00:48.283
[ Rapid beeping ]

00:48.352 --> 00:51.520
Chief: I was born to
do this operation.

00:51.556 --> 00:56.142
<font color="#ec14bd">Sync & corrections by honeybunny</font>
<font color="#ec14bd">www.addic7ed.com</font>

00:56.262 --> 01:00.199
Chief: How could I screw up this
operation that I was <i>born to do?</i>

01:00.235 --> 01:04.105
<i>Lola: You keep saying that, chief,
with great unearned bravado.</i>

01:04.140 --> 01:05.173
<i>How were you born to do it?</i>

01:05.208 --> 01:09.746
<i>Chief: That, my friends, is a long,
long, long, long, crazy long story.</i>

01:09.815 --> 01:11.648
<i>Lola: Yeah, so you probably
shouldn't tell it.</i>

01:11.718 --> 01:13.651
<i>Owen: Yeah, we can just
check your blog, right?</i>

01:13.685 --> 01:18.389
<i>Chief: I was born in a mobile home on
a poor Choctaw Indian reservation.</i>

01:18.457 --> 01:22.126
<i>You have blessed the earth,
mother, with a baby girl.</i>

01:22.161 --> 01:24.629
<i>What will you call
this future leader?</i>

01:24.664 --> 01:29.633
<i>I shall call her...um...
Oh, uh, chief.</i>

01:29.668 --> 01:31.769
<i>I shall call her chief.</i>

01:31.837 --> 01:35.473
<i>Does the child have
any deformities?</i>

01:35.542 --> 01:36.040
<i>What?</i>

01:36.076 --> 01:37.775
<i>Is something wrong
with little whore?</i>

01:37.844 --> 01:38.777
<i>Wait, no. Sorry.</i>

01:38.845 --> 01:40.212
<i>Thought I saw something.</i>

01:40.247 --> 01:41.113
<i>She's totally fine.</i>

01:41.148 --> 01:42.114
<i>Oh. Thank goodness.</i>

01:42.183 --> 01:43.316
<i>Chief: ♪ Hello, my baby ♪</i>

01:43.351 --> 01:44.217
<i>♪ hello, my honey ♪</i>

01:44.285 --> 01:45.318
<i>Isn't that something?</i>

01:45.353 --> 01:47.053
<i>Chief: ♪ Hello, my ragtime gal ♪</i>

01:47.088 --> 01:48.455
<i>♪ send me a kiss by wire ♪</i>

01:48.490 --> 01:50.223
<i>♪ baby, ma heart's on fire ♪</i>

01:50.259 --> 01:51.758
<i>I wonder when it will stop?</i>

01:51.827 --> 01:54.128
<i>Chief: That's right, my friends.</i>

01:54.163 --> 01:57.699
<i>I, too, spent most of my life
spontaneously bursting into song.</i>

01:57.767 --> 01:59.233
<i>But...I was able to cure myself.</i>

01:59.302 --> 02:00.201
<i>Valerie: The end!</i>

02:00.236 --> 02:01.769
<i>Chief: No, no, it's not the end.</i>

02:01.805 --> 02:03.038
<i>Valerie: Wow, chief.</i>

02:03.073 --> 02:05.240
<i>Your storytelling is as
crappy as your doctoring.</i>

02:05.276 --> 02:06.241
<i>Can we go now?</i>

02:06.277 --> 02:10.680
<i>Sy: Valerie, if you were half the
doctor that chief was, you'd be lucky.</i>

02:10.715 --> 02:11.681
<i>But you're not.</i>

02:11.750 --> 02:16.053
You're fully the doctor that you are,
which is to say not as good.

02:16.088 --> 02:16.787
Valerie: Well, geez, Sy.

02:16.823 --> 02:18.522
If you love chief that much,
why don't you marry her?

02:18.591 --> 02:20.625
Sy: Hey, I would marry
the chief three times.

02:20.694 --> 02:23.162
I would bear her
overweight children.

02:23.197 --> 02:26.598
I would pat her handicapped
forehead, and I would cradle her

02:26.667 --> 02:30.302
if she died her foul-smelling
and painful death, before I let

02:30.338 --> 02:33.806
you put one <i>foot</i> in a room with
someone who is just putting a

02:33.841 --> 02:38.178
band-aid on my skinned knee...
a-hole.

02:38.246 --> 02:39.346
You understand?

02:39.414 --> 02:40.814
Valerie: Yes, sir.

02:40.849 --> 02:41.782
Sorry, sir.

02:41.817 --> 02:47.255
Sy: Now, all of you -- everyone is going
to listen to the chief's stories.

02:47.323 --> 02:48.623
No daydreaming!

02:48.658 --> 02:52.160
Chief: Thank you, Sy.

02:52.196 --> 02:54.796
Sy: Thank you so much for
yelling at Valerie, Jerry.

02:54.832 --> 02:57.633
Jerry: Ah, the old twin-brother
Switcheroo works every time.

02:57.702 --> 03:00.003
Sy: Well, you know, I'm not
good at confrontation.

03:00.038 --> 03:02.372
Jerry: Try growing a mustache.

03:02.407 --> 03:04.374
Both: [ Laugh ]

03:04.409 --> 03:07.077
Chief: Then, midday the
following week, I had a similar

03:07.112 --> 03:09.646
feeling as the day before,
although <i>very</i> different from the

03:09.714 --> 03:11.447
way I was feeling
over the weekend.

03:11.516 --> 03:13.183
[ Distorted ] But...
Jerry: ...Sticking a band-aid

03:13.218 --> 03:16.353
on my skinned knee...a-hole.

03:16.389 --> 03:17.621
You understand?

03:17.656 --> 03:20.024
Valerie: You know what, Sy?

03:20.092 --> 03:21.793
Why don't you go jump in a lake?

03:21.828 --> 03:23.461
Chief: Oh, no, you didn't!

03:23.496 --> 03:25.163
Lola: Can you even imagine?

03:25.198 --> 03:26.364
Sy jumping in a lake?!

03:26.433 --> 03:28.033
Chief: It's all about you.

03:28.102 --> 03:30.002
You know what I
mean, right, Val?

03:30.070 --> 03:30.736
Right, Val?

03:30.804 --> 03:33.572
I mean, isn't that
what you always say?

03:33.608 --> 03:35.007
Valerie: Yeah, of course.

03:35.076 --> 03:35.808
That's what I say.

03:35.844 --> 03:39.179
If I don't say it, who will, because
they're not me so they can't.

03:39.214 --> 03:40.113
So nobody. Just me.

03:40.182 --> 03:41.815
I'll say it. I always say it.

03:41.850 --> 03:45.219
Chief: The point is, my
life was not an easy one.

03:45.254 --> 03:48.122
No school would take me,
so I was home a lot.

03:48.157 --> 03:50.291
♪ My Bonnie lies
over the ocean ♪

03:50.360 --> 03:52.226
♪ my Bonnie lies over the sea ♪

03:52.295 --> 03:56.664
My father didn't work, so he was
home, too, until he wasn't.

03:56.700 --> 03:58.199
Oh, man!

03:58.235 --> 03:59.200
I'm out of here, man.

03:59.235 --> 04:02.470
Chief: ♪ Bring back,
oh, bring back ♪

04:02.505 --> 04:06.307
♪ mid pleasures and palaces ♪

04:06.376 --> 04:09.143
I tried to cure it by performing
brain surgery on myself.

04:09.212 --> 04:11.045
♪ Though we may roam ♪

04:11.080 --> 04:15.683
The first few operations were...
unsuccessful.

04:15.752 --> 04:17.051
♪ There's no... ♪

04:17.120 --> 04:20.755
That "operation" permanently
damaged my eyesight and that is

04:20.790 --> 04:24.692
when I started having to wear
these thick, ugly glasses.

04:24.728 --> 04:27.762
The wrist guards, of course, are
another story, a fascinating

04:27.798 --> 04:29.698
one -- rather
amusing, if you will.

04:29.767 --> 04:33.669
I first saw these wrist guards...
Jerry: ...My skinned knee, a-hole.

04:33.704 --> 04:34.670
Do you understand?

04:34.705 --> 04:36.238
Valerie: Yes, sir.

04:36.307 --> 04:37.239
Sorry, sir.

04:37.274 --> 04:38.307
Blake: Val.

04:38.342 --> 04:40.476
Let me handle this.

04:40.511 --> 04:42.611
Leave her alone, Sy.

04:42.680 --> 04:45.247
And, while you're at it, why
don't you go jump in a lake?

04:45.316 --> 04:46.248
Owen: Yes!

04:46.283 --> 04:48.150
Lola: Can you even imagine?

04:48.185 --> 04:49.518
Sy jumping in a lake?!

04:49.553 --> 04:51.052
That's priceless, man.

04:51.121 --> 04:52.754
Valerie: What a man.

04:52.790 --> 04:56.692
We've been waiting too long
for this, right, Blake?

04:56.760 --> 04:58.426
Right, Blake?

04:58.462 --> 04:59.394
Blake.

04:59.429 --> 05:01.529
Chief: Blake, are you
following me or not?

05:01.598 --> 05:02.263
Blake: No. No.

05:02.332 --> 05:04.398
I got to get back
to my daydream!

05:04.434 --> 05:07.602
Valerie: Welcome back, Blake.

05:07.637 --> 05:09.504
This is my body.

05:09.539 --> 05:12.339
Soon, it will be yours.

05:18.714 --> 05:21.349
Blake: [ Breathing heavily ]

05:21.418 --> 05:22.250
Hmm.

05:22.285 --> 05:26.188
Chief: I then embarked on a
period of self-experimentation,

05:26.223 --> 05:27.723
determined to find a cure.

05:27.791 --> 05:31.360
When I was old enough, I went
to med school and started

05:31.429 --> 05:36.365
experimenting on cadavers.

05:36.434 --> 05:39.435
And we all experimented
in college, right?

05:39.470 --> 05:43.539
Finally, I had the training to
operate on my own brain in the

05:43.574 --> 05:45.374
right way, or so I hoped.

05:45.410 --> 05:46.375
Ow!

05:48.579 --> 05:50.079
But... dang it!

05:50.115 --> 05:51.648
...I kept experimenting.

05:51.716 --> 05:55.718
I graduated at the top of my
class, but my list of handicaps

05:55.754 --> 06:01.191
had grown -- the walker, this almost
cartoonish hunch, the ugly wig.

06:01.259 --> 06:03.560
Finally, I finished
my internship.

06:03.628 --> 06:06.029
Chief, you finally
finished your internship.

06:06.098 --> 06:07.664
Chief: Okay, good.

06:07.699 --> 06:09.733
Oh, it had gone by so fast.

06:09.801 --> 06:14.170
Twinkling... Chief finally
finished her internship.

06:14.206 --> 06:15.005
Lola: What?

06:15.040 --> 06:16.373
Oh, my daydreams suck.

06:16.408 --> 06:21.211
Chief: And now the day of the
operation was finally upon me.

06:21.279 --> 06:26.182
The operation lasted for what
seemed like days, and I sang the

06:26.217 --> 06:31.021
entire time...until I stopped.

06:33.257 --> 06:37.560
I'm cured...of everything!

06:37.596 --> 06:39.663
All of my handicaps are gone!

06:39.698 --> 06:40.664
[ Chuckles ]

06:40.732 --> 06:42.032
Let's celebrate!

06:42.067 --> 06:46.503
So, instead of singing, I danced,
with my friend Wayne, a male nurse.

06:46.538 --> 06:48.371
Kind of a drama queen.

06:48.407 --> 06:50.373
And that's the end of my story!

06:50.409 --> 06:53.143
Lola: But, chief, if I was
listening correctly -- and the

06:53.178 --> 06:55.778
answer is, no, I was not -- you
said that you were cured <i>all</i>

06:55.847 --> 06:59.214
<i>your handicaps in that operation,
but you clearly still have them.</i>

06:59.250 --> 07:00.416
<i>Chief: [ Laughing ] Okay.</i>

07:00.451 --> 07:03.285
That is a <i>really</i> funny story.

07:03.320 --> 07:05.054
Blake: Bet you it
won't be funny.

07:05.122 --> 07:07.589
Chief: So, the same thing
with the dancing, no singing,

07:07.625 --> 07:15.496
Wayne, et cetera, and...
Wayne: N-o-o-o-o-o!!

07:15.565 --> 07:19.000
[ Sobbing ] Oh, no!

07:19.069 --> 07:21.169
Why?!

07:21.238 --> 07:22.370
No!!

07:22.405 --> 07:23.538
Chief: [ Laughs ]

07:23.573 --> 07:25.640
Blake: Said it
wouldn't be funny.

07:25.675 --> 07:27.742
Chief: Oh, man, did that hurt!

07:27.811 --> 07:28.643
Oh, God.

07:28.712 --> 07:32.513
I mean, that Wayne was
such a drama queen.

07:32.548 --> 07:35.183
[ Heroic music plays ]

07:38.820 --> 07:40.288
Owen: [ Screams ]

07:40.356 --> 07:42.656
Owen: No!!

07:42.692 --> 07:45.426
No! [ Sobbing ]

07:51.266 --> 07:52.833
Blake: Hey, man.

07:52.869 --> 07:55.536
You were talking in your sleep.

07:55.571 --> 07:58.272
Me, me, me, me, and I'm perfect.

07:58.308 --> 07:59.273
Owen: Oh, yeah.

07:59.309 --> 08:00.641
Valerie: Chief, I get it.

08:00.677 --> 08:02.643
You <i>were</i> born to do that operation.

08:02.678 --> 08:04.378
Chief: But then why did it fail?

08:04.447 --> 08:05.212
Lola: Wait.

08:05.248 --> 08:06.447
Chief, what are you drinking?

08:06.482 --> 08:07.548
Chief: My coffee. Why?

08:07.583 --> 08:08.749
Lola: That's not coffee!

08:08.818 --> 08:10.117
Chief: Parkinson's juice?

08:10.186 --> 08:12.353
Owen: Parkinson's disease
makes your hands shake.

08:12.388 --> 08:13.554
That's why the surgery failed.

08:13.589 --> 08:16.022
Chief: Oh, my God, you're right!

08:16.091 --> 08:20.293
And if I fail, which I won't, I will
happily turn in my resignation.

08:20.362 --> 08:22.195
Turn in my resignation.

08:22.231 --> 08:25.666
I...was...born to
do this operation.

08:25.701 --> 08:27.267
Steady as she goes.

08:27.302 --> 08:28.668
Mystery solved, huh?

08:28.737 --> 08:33.139
I guess it all boiled down to
me drinking Parkinson's juice.

08:33.207 --> 08:34.140
Okay, pals.

08:34.208 --> 08:37.777
Well, thanks for list...
Owen: Oh, hey, Derrick.

08:37.813 --> 08:40.046
Chief: Thanks for listening.

08:40.115 --> 08:41.114
And that's it.

08:41.149 --> 08:45.185
That's the story of how I told
the story of my life to these

08:45.220 --> 08:47.487
other doctors who I
used to work with.

08:47.522 --> 08:49.322
Those doctors sound
like a bunch of dicks.

08:49.391 --> 08:51.324
At least we listen
when you tell stories.

08:51.359 --> 08:53.592
Chief: Oh, it doesn't
matter, anyway.

08:53.661 --> 08:54.827
They're all dead now.

08:54.862 --> 08:55.594
Right, Sy?

08:55.663 --> 08:56.495
Right, Jerry?

08:56.564 --> 09:00.033
Jerry: They just didn't listen.

09:01.769 --> 09:02.702
Lola: Hey, Sy.

09:02.771 --> 09:05.305
[ Gasps ]

09:10.678 --> 09:13.246
Owen: No, no, no, no! Blake!

09:17.451 --> 09:21.754
Valerie: [ Gasps, screams ]

09:21.790 --> 09:24.524
[ Bear growls ]

09:28.262 --> 09:31.131
Owen: [ Thinking ] Look
at all these articles.

09:31.167 --> 09:32.599
Why did you all have to die?

09:32.668 --> 09:33.534
Who <i>did</i> this?

09:33.569 --> 09:37.404
Wait a second.

09:39.507 --> 09:42.176
Oh, my God!

09:44.379 --> 09:46.680
[ Screams ]

09:52.853 --> 09:54.354
Chief: [ Laughs ]

09:54.389 --> 09:58.625
And that completes the story
of how Sy and Jerry murdered a

09:58.661 --> 10:03.730
bunch of doctors because
they were bad listeners.

10:03.799 --> 10:05.265
And that's the whole story.

10:05.334 --> 10:08.168
We were in her office, and they
told us in detail how each of

10:08.237 --> 10:09.436
the murders was committed.

10:09.471 --> 10:12.339
I guess you could say I was born
to get her to tell her story.

10:12.374 --> 10:13.373
What do you mean?

10:13.408 --> 10:14.641
[ Chuckles ]

10:14.676 --> 10:20.080
Well, that's a long,
long, long, long story.

10:20.149 --> 10:24.452
[ Laughing maniacally ]

10:29.892 --> 10:32.460
[ Maniacal laughing continues ]

10:32.580 --> 10:43.288
<font color="#ec14bd">Sync & corrections by honeybunny</font>
<font color="#ec14bd">www.addic7ed.com</font>

10:45.991 --> 10:47.492
Sal: <i>Attention, staff.</i>

10:47.527 --> 10:49.060
<i>You say Parkinson's.</i>

10:49.096 --> 10:50.895
<i>I say pock-in-son's.</i>

10:50.964 --> 10:52.397
<i>That is all.</i>
